text: Canby is an unincorporated community in Adair County, in the U.S. state of Iowa. ==History== A post office called Canby was established in 1873, and remained in operation until 1908. A Quaker church once stood near the town site. Little remains of the original community. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Adair County, Iowa Category:Unincorporated communities in Iowa
title: Canby, Iowa
